Remove outliers¶

In [30]:
Q1 = numerical_features.quantile(0.25)
Q3 = numerical_features.quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

# plt.figure(figsize=(15,10))
# ax = sns.countplot(y = IQR)
In [31]:
if REMOVE_OUTLIARS:
    iqr_cols = IQR.index
    numerical_features = numerical_features[~( (numerical_features[iqr_cols] < (Q1[iqr_cols] - 1.5 * IQR[iqr_cols])) | (numerical_features[iqr_cols] > (Q3[iqr_cols] + 1.5 * IQR[iqr_cols])) ).any(axis=1)]
    cat_features = cat_features.loc[numerical_features.index]
    labels = labels.loc[numerical_features.index]

false_label = _X[_X[:, -1] == 0]
true_label = _X[_X[:, -1] == 1]

false_label_downsampled = resample(false_label,
                                replace = False, # sample without replacement
                                n_samples = len(false_label), # match minority n
                                random_state = 1) # reproducible results


true_label_upsampled = resample(true_label,
                          replace=True, # sample with replacement
                          n_samples=len(true_label), # match number in majority class
                          random_state=1) # reproducible results


_X = np.concatenate((false_label_downsampled, true_label_upsampled),axis=0)
_X_train, _y_train = _X[:,:-1], _X[:,-1]
